<db:section xml:id="platform-plugin-dependencies">
<db:title>Platform Plugin Dependencies</db:title>
<db:para>On Linux, the <db:emphasis>xcb</db:emphasis> QPA (Qt Platform Abstraction) platform plugin is used. It provides the basic functionality needed by <db:link xlink:href="qtgui-index.xml">Qt GUI</db:link> and <db:link xlink:href="qtwidgets-index.xml">Qt Widgets</db:link> to run against X11. Its library dependencies are described the following table. To build Qt from its source code, you will also need to install the development packages for these libraries for your system.</db:para>
<db:note>
<db:para>From Qt 5.15 onwards, Qt does require libxcb 1.11. Also, the -qt-xcb configure option got removed that was bundling some of the libs below. Anyhow, you can now configure with -bundled-xcb-xinput to avoid a dependency to system xcb-xinput.</db:para>
